Group Name

Mold-like Substance

Inspection Summary

  • Inspection type: Mold Inspection
  • Purpose of Inspection: To assess the presence and severity of mold-like substances and elevated moisture levels within the property.
  • Deficiencies Violated: DEFICIENCY 2 � INSIDE: PRESENCE OF MOLD-LIKE SUBSTANCE AT HIGH LEVELS IS OBSERVED VISUALLY
  • Overall Findings: Immediate remediation is recommended for the mold-like substance observed inside, as it poses moderate health risks.

Deficiencies

Source

NSPIRE-Standard-Mold-like-Substance_20230811.pdf

Detailed Findings

Deficiency:DEFICIENCY 2 � INSIDE: PRESENCE OF MOLD-LIKE SUBSTANCE AT HIGH LEVELS IS OBSERVED VISUALLY.

  • Title: MOLD-LIKE SUBSTANCE
  • Violation: Yes
  • Description: The Image_data matches this deficiency, as the mold infestation spans areas ranging from 3 to 6 square feet, which fits the criteria of more than 1 square foot and less than 9 square feet. The location 'INSIDE' also matches exactly.
  • Recommendation: Immediate remediation is recommended to prevent further mold growth and mitigate health risks associated with mold exposure.
  • HCV_fail_Pass: Fail
  • HCV_correction_timeframe: 30 days
  • Severity: Moderate
  • Criteria_in_policy_document: Cumulative area of patches is more than 1 square foot and less than 9 square feet in a room.

Deficiency:DEFICIENCY 1 � UNIT: PRESENCE OF MOLD-LIKE SUBSTANCE AT MODERATE LEVELS IS OBSERVED VISUALLY.

  • Title: MOLD-LIKE SUBSTANCE
  • Violation: No
  • Description: The deficiency found in the Image_data does not match the criteria for 'DEFICIENCY 1 � UNIT', as the mold spans areas ranging from 3 to 6 square feet, which does not fit the criteria of more than 4 square inches and less than 1 square foot.
  • Recommendation: Not Applicable
  • HCV_fail_Pass: Fail
  • HCV_correction_timeframe: 30 days
  • Severity: Moderate
  • Criteria_in_policy_document: Cumulative area of patches is more than 4 square inches and less than 1 square foot in a room.
